<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Almost endemic to the Distrito Federal and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Goiás">Goias</normalizedToken>
State in Brazil. It appears to grow always in campo rupestre from around 800 m to over 1100 m. It is recorded from Mato Grosso in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction but we have seen no specimen.
